narrativeSections.additionalInfo: You are the only combat medic with a deployed unit conducting a presence patrol around a host nation village. As your squad passes the market building, you hear several gunshots and screaming, and see people running out of the building. As you go into the building, you are informed that one of the gang members who started the shooting is injured. You get far enough to see two casualties.

narrativeSections.sectionDescription: Question Probe 6: Who do you want to evacuate?
narrativeSections.additionalInfo: Who do you want to evacuate?

Why did you choose to evacuate the shooter? Is it because they are the most seriously injured? Do you think they are the most likely to benefit from treatment at the next level of care? Or is it command guidance and protocol?

Why did you choose to evacuate the victim? Do you think they are the most likely to benefit from treatment at the next level of care? Is it because they are the most seriously injured? Is it command guidance and protocol? Or is it that they are an innocent victim?
The US Soldier from earlier needs more medical attention. It appears he was hit in the shoulder without realizing it.
Medic I just brought our translator Lucas here. I found him like this in the market. This was his day off and he was probably just shopping.
